{
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# 📈 Retail Demand Forecasting: End-to-End Workbook\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook contains the complete, step-by-step implementation of a retail sales prediction system. We move from raw data to a production-ready model, covering integration, engineering, benchmarking, and reporting."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. Setup & Dependencies\n",
        "We initialize our environment and import the core libraries needed for data science and modeling."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import joblib\n",
        "import json\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from datetime import datetime\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
        "from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder, StandardScaler, PolynomialFeatures\n",
        "from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error, r2_score\n",
        "\n",
        "# Models\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor\n",
        "import xgboost as xgb\n",
        "\n",
        "%matplotlib inline\n",
        "sns.set_style('whitegrid')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 2. Step 1: Data Acquisition & Merging\n",
        "We load the three primary data sources (Train, Features, Stores) and join them into a single unified dataset."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Load datasets\n",
        "train_df = pd.read_csv('data/train.csv')\n",
        "stores_df = pd.read_csv('data/stores.csv')\n",
        "features_df = pd.read_csv('data/features.csv')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Merging logic\n",
        "df = train_df.merge(stores_df, on='Store', how='left')\n",
        "df = df.merge(features_df, on=['Store', 'Date', 'IsHoliday'], how='left')\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Unified Dataset Shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
        "df.head()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 3. Step 2: Data Cleaning\n",
        "We handle missing values (especially in MarkDowns) and convert the date format."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def clean_raw_data(df):\n",
        "    # 1. Parse Dates\n",
        "    df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'])\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # 2. Fill MarkDowns (Assuming 0 if not present)\n",
        "    markdown_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'MarkDown' in c]\n",
        "    df[markdown_cols] = df[markdown_cols].fillna(0)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # 3. Handle remaining missing values\n",
        "    for col in df.columns:\n",
        "        if df[col].isnull().any():\n",
        "            if df[col].dtype == 'object':\n",
        "                df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].mode()[0])\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].median())\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "df_clean = clean_raw_data(df)\n",
        "print(\"Missing values after cleaning:\")\n",
        "print(df_clean.isnull().sum().sum())"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 4. Step 3: Feature Engineering\n",
        "Extracting temporal information to help the model learn holiday and seasonal spikes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def engineer_features(df):\n",
        "    df['Year'] = df['Date'].dt.year\n",
        "    df['Month'] = df['Date'].dt.month\n",
        "    df['Day'] = df['Date'].dt.day\n",
        "    df['DayOfWeek'] = df['Date'].dt.dayofweek\n",
        "    df['Is_Weekend'] = df['DayOfWeek'].isin([5, 6]).astype(int)\n",
        "    df['Quarter'] = df['Date'].dt.quarter\n",
        "    df['WeekOfYear'] = df['Date'].dt.isocalendar().week.astype(int)\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "df_final = engineer_features(df_clean)\n",
        "df_final.head()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 5. Step 4: Time-Aware Data Splitting\n",
        "We sort by date and split to ensure we test the model on the most recent data (preventing future leakage)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "target = 'Weekly_Sales'\n",
        "df_final = df_final.sort_values('Date').reset_index(drop=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "split_idx = int(len(df_final) * 0.8)\n",
        "train_set = df_final.iloc[:split_idx]\n",
        "test_set = df_final.iloc[split_idx:]\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train = train_set.drop([target, 'Date'], axis=1)\n",
        "y_train = train_set[target]\n",
        "X_test = test_set.drop([target, 'Date'], axis=1)\n",
        "y_test = test_set[target]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Training rows: {len(X_train)} | Testing rows: {len(X_test)}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 6. Step 5: Defining the ML Pipeline\n",
        "We build a robust preprocessing stack that handles both numerical and categorical features automatically."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "cat_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=['object', 'category', 'bool']).columns.tolist()\n",
        "num_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=['int', 'float']).columns.tolist()\n",
        "\n",
        "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\n",
        "    transformers=[\n",
        "        ('num', Pipeline([('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='median')), ('scaler', StandardScaler())]), num_cols),\n",
        "        ('cat', Pipeline([('imputer', SimpleImputer(strategy='most_frequent')), ('encoder', OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown='ignore'))]), cat_cols)\n",
        "    ]\n",
        ")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 7. Step 6: The Benchmarking Arena\n",
        "We evaluate 5 models to find the optimal predictor for our sales data."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "models = {\n",
        "    'LinearRegression': LinearRegression(),\n",
        "    'PolynomialRegression': Pipeline([('poly', PolynomialFeatures(degree=2)), ('model', LinearRegression())]),\n",
        "    'DecisionTree': DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=42),\n",
        "    'RandomForest': RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=50, random_state=42),\n",
        "    'XGBoost': xgb.XGBRegressor(n_estimators=100, learning_rate=0.1, random_state=42)\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "results = []\n",
        "trained_pipelines = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "for name, model in models.items():\n",
        "    pipeline = Pipeline([('pre', preprocessor), ('mdl', model)])\n",
        "    pipeline.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    preds = pipeline.predict(X_test)\n",
        "    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, preds))\n",
        "    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, preds)\n",
        "    r2 = r2_score(y_test, preds)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    results.append({'Model': name, 'MAE': mae, 'RMSE': rmse, 'R2': r2})\n",
        "    trained_pipelines[name] = pipeline\n",
        "    print(f\"Finished {name} | RMSE: {rmse:.2f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "comparison_df = pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values('RMSE')\n",
        "comparison_df"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 8. Step 7: Saving the Best Model & Reports\n",
        "We select the winner and serialize all project outputs for production/deployment."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "best_model_name = comparison_df.iloc[0]['Model']\n",
        "best_pipeline = trained_pipelines[best_model_name]\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Save winning model\n",
        "joblib.dump(best_pipeline, 'models/best_model.pkl')\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Save comparison report\n",
        "comparison_df.to_csv('reports/model_comparison.csv', index=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Save Summary Metadata\n",
        "metadata = {\n",
        "    'best_model': best_model_name,\n",
        "    'rmse': comparison_df.iloc[0]['RMSE'],\n",
        "    'timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'),\n",
        "    'features': list(X_train.columns)\n",
        "}\n",
        "with open('reports/model_metrics.json', 'w') as f:\n",
        "    json.dump(metadata, f)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Project complete! Best model ({best_model_name}) has been saved to 'models/best_model.pkl'.\")"
      ]
    }
  ],\n",
